13:51.613 --> 13:53.789
What are you doing?

13:53.876 --> 13:55.095
[sighs]

13:55.182 --> 13:56.096
I need a meeting.

13:56.183 --> 13:58.620
Here?
Why not?

13:58.707 --> 14:00.709
We'’ve got four drunks
and a bunch of crappy snacks.

14:00.796 --> 14:02.189
Sounds like a meeting to me.

14:02.276 --> 14:03.755
All right.

14:03.843 --> 14:05.714
I guess we'’re
having a meeting.

14:09.936 --> 14:13.287
Welcome to the Interstate 5,

14:13.374 --> 14:17.160
mile marker 23 meeting
of Alcoholics Anonymous.

14:17.247 --> 14:18.596
I'’ll start.

14:18.683 --> 14:20.685
[sighs]

14:20.772 --> 14:22.644
Hi, I'’m Christy.
I'’m an alcoholic.

14:22.731 --> 14:24.385
ALL:
Hi, Christy.

14:26.778 --> 14:28.476
I know we joke a lot

14:28.563 --> 14:31.218
about all the crazy stuff we did

14:31.305 --> 14:33.220
when we were drunk and loaded.

14:33.307 --> 14:35.439
[sniffs]

14:35.526 --> 14:39.095
And maybe it'’s funny
'’cause we got away with it.

14:39.182 --> 14:40.792
We'’re still here.

14:44.013 --> 14:45.885
But Jodi'’s not.

14:48.583 --> 14:50.541
And I'’ve got to find some way

14:50.628 --> 14:53.022
to make sense of that.

14:53.109 --> 14:56.634
Otherwise, her dying is just...

14:56.721 --> 14:59.159
a complete waste.

15:02.814 --> 15:06.949
We have to make it
mean something.

15:07.036 --> 15:08.908
I have to...

15:11.301 --> 15:14.391
...make it mean something.

15:14.478 --> 15:15.479
[sighs]

15:15.566 --> 15:17.177
And the only way I can do that

15:17.264 --> 15:20.136
is by never taking
my sobriety for granted.

15:21.964 --> 15:24.924
I don'’t know how many
second chances I'’ll get.

15:25.011 --> 15:26.926
I'’ve had eight.

15:28.492 --> 15:30.016
Anyway...

15:30.103 --> 15:31.017
[clears throat]

15:31.104 --> 15:33.019
That'’s it.

15:33.106 --> 15:34.716
Would anyone else like to share?

15:37.371 --> 15:39.547
I'’m not following that.

15:39.634 --> 15:41.418
I think you said it all.

15:42.637 --> 15:45.335
Okay.

15:45.422 --> 15:46.641
Serenity Prayer.

15:46.728 --> 15:47.642
[sniffs]

15:47.729 --> 15:48.643
[clears throat]

15:50.645 --> 15:51.907
God...

15:51.994 --> 15:53.996
ALL:
...grant me the serenity

15:54.083 --> 15:56.477
to accept the things
I cannot change,

15:56.564 --> 16:00.133
the courage to change
the things I can

16:00.220 --> 16:04.311
and the wisdom
to know the difference.

16:04.398 --> 16:06.269
ALL: Amen.

16:22.590 --> 16:24.505
[knocking]

16:26.898 --> 16:28.509
Hi.

16:28.596 --> 16:30.206
Hi.

16:30.293 --> 16:31.773
This a bad time?

16:31.860 --> 16:33.993
That depends.

16:34.080 --> 16:35.733
Are you gonna yell at me?

16:35.820 --> 16:37.039
No.

16:37.126 --> 16:38.780
Then come on in.

16:43.002 --> 16:43.915
You want some tea?

16:44.003 --> 16:45.874
Uh, no, thanks.

16:45.961 --> 16:49.008
So... what'’s up?

16:49.095 --> 16:51.575
I'’m here because
I owe you an amends.

16:51.662 --> 16:53.012
Really?

16:53.099 --> 16:55.231
Yeah, really.

16:55.318 --> 16:57.407
I know your heart
was in the right place

16:57.494 --> 16:59.366
